{{primary|date=August 2017}} {{Infobox journal | title = Greek, Roman, and Byzantine Studies | discipline = [[Classics]] | abbreviation = | editors = Joshua D. Sosin, José Gonzáles | publisher = [[Duke University Press]] | country = United States | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1958-present | website = https://grbs.library.duke.edu/ | ISSN = }} '''''Greek, Roman, and Byzantine Studies''''' is a quarterly [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] established in 1958 by John J. Bilitz. It is published by [[Duke University Press]] and devoted to the culture and history of Greece from Antiquity to the Renaissance, featuring research on all aspects of the Hellenic world from [[prehistoric Greece|prehistoric antiquity]] through the [[Ancient Greece|Ancient Greek]], [[Roman Empire|Roman]], and [[Byzantine Empire|Byzantine]] periods, including studies of modern classical scholarship. The [[editors-in-chief]] are Joshua D. Sosin and José Gonzáles (Duke University). Kent J. Rigsby is associate editor.
